            <p> 
            Craljax is an open source, web-crawling tool written in Java for crawling and testing modern web applications. It creates a state-flow diagram of the DOM states and the events that causes the transitions between the states. 
            </p>
            <p>
                As my final project for a Software Engineering course in UBC, I've contribute to the project with a team of four fellow students. Using agile development practices such as TDD, user stories and sprint planning, we've successfully fixed two issues:
                <ul>
                    <li><%= link_to "Issue #135: ", "https://github.com/crawljax/crawljax/issues/135", target: "_blank" %> Improving Crawl configurations with clever XPath manipulation. </li>
                    <li><%= link_to "Issue #151: ", "https://github.com/crawljax/crawljax/issues/151", target: "_blank" %>Refactor two similar classes into one single class.</li>
                </ul>
                Our Pull Request for Issue #135 has been merged to master but unfortunately for Issue #151, someone else submitted a pull request before us and ours did not get accepted.
            </p>   
