        <div class="project-content">
          <div class="section-header">
            <h2 class="anchor" id="sentiment">Sentiment Analysis Mashup</h2>
            <small>
                <%= link_to "Link to code", "https://github.com/chris-yoon90/sentiment_analysis"%>
            </small>
          </div>
          <%= image_tag("sentiment_analysis_img.jpg", size: "600x450")%>
          <p>
            This is a quick mashup application I've made with <%= link_to "colinmleung", "https://github.com/colinmleung", target: "_blank"%> to analyze reddit and twitter posts based on their sentiment. For example, a user can type in a keyword to a search box and the application will return the first nine results from Reddit or Twitter relating to the keyword. But that's not all. The web application is hooked up to a sentiment analysis API that can analyze the content and give it a score based on their sentiment.
          </p>
          <p>
            The application used to work for both Reddit and Twitter, but after Twitter's API change to v1.1, Twitter side will not work anymore because: <%= link_to '"every request to the API to be authenticated"', "https://dev.twitter.com/blog/changes-coming-to-twitter-api", target: "_blank"%> (dated August, 2012). However, the application should still work with Reddit.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've attempted, a few months back, to re-write this application in Ruby on Rails and improve the UI design but I've been busy with work, school and other projects. Hopefully, I'll get to work on it sometime later. <%= link_to "New_sentiment_analysis", "https://github.com/chris-yoon90/new_sentiment_analysis", target: "_blank" %>
          </p>

